Steven Jeffery added: ‘FFS Cadbury!! You expect us Aussies to support you & continue to buy your products... But you are continuously down grading your products!! Be fair now!!’

The change is expected to affect the standard milk chocolate blocks along with the many variations including the fruit and nut, rocky road, Crunchie flavoured and Turkish Delight versions.

Cadbury chocolate produced for the Australian market is made in Claremont in Tasmania.

A statement on the company’s website reads: ‘Over the next few weeks, you will see something different about Cadbury family blocks. While our commitment to providing the same taste and quality of Cadbury chocolate you love remains, you will see a change in the size of our 210g/220g family blocks.’

